Offre VIE VIE231682 - ERP SYSTEMS ANALYST (H/F)
    Entreprise: DEMGY NORMANDIE
    Localisation: TACOMA (WA), ETATS-UNIS
    Secteur d'activité: INDUSTRIES CHIMIQUES ET PLASTURGIE
    Durée: 6 mois
    Indemnité: 3674 € par mois
    Description de la mission: Présentation de la société :

DEMGY Pacific est une entreprise américaine spécialisée dans la fabrication de pièces plastiques et métalliques pour l’aéronautique. Basée à Tacoma (Washington), elle fait partie du groupe DEMGY depuis 2025

Poste et missions :

ERP system optimization:  
- Current challenge:  the IQMS ERP system contains data and information that is unreliable.  This lack of reliability results in scheduling issues, production/delivery delays, and overproduction 
- Objective:
o Work with the Demgy Pacific team to analyze causes for ERP data issues and the reasons.  Recommend and implement solutions to eliminate the need for workarounds
o Analyze MRP run quantity settings that are currently leading to production inefficiencies (e.g., minimum run quantities, work order bundling, etc).  Recommend and implement solutions that will result in optimized inventory and equipment utilization
o Analyze BOM settings and provide recommendations to improve BOM cycle time and material consumption accuracy

ERP system consolidation:  
- Current challenge:  Demgy Pacific currently operates with two ERP systems -- IQMS for the Plastics Division and Jobboss for the Metals Division.  This results in lack of visibility between the two divisions, inability to share resources, and the requirement for dual accounting systems, ordering systems, purchasing systems, etc. 
- Objective:  work with the Demgy Pacific team to develop and implement a plan to consolidate all Jobboss activity into IQMS

Offre VIE VIE231189 - EMBEDDED LINUX ENGINEER (YOCTO) (M/F)
    Entreprise: WITEKIO HOLDING
    Localisation: BELLEVUE        -WA-                    , ETATS-UNIS
    Secteur d'activité: TECHNOLOGIES DE L'INFORMATION ET DES TELECOMMUNICATIONS
    Durée: 18 mois
    Indemnité: 3674 € par mois
    Description de la mission: Are you fascinated by embedded technologies and eager to work on innovative software projects? Take a look at this position!

Witekio helps device makers bring their products to life with world-class software!

With 20+ years of experience and a team of 150+ passionate employees, we work across many industries to help our clients accelerate time to market, level up products, and reduce project risks. We love to solve problems with design and technology. We offer full-stack, edge-to-cloud embedded development services.

Witekio is headquartered in Lyon and has five office locations across four countries, including the USA, UK, France, and Germany. Witekio is also part of Avnet - a Fortune 500 company.

Want to know more? Have a look to our case studies:  https://witekio.com/category/case-studies/



Context

We are looking for an Embedded Linux Engineer to provide ongoing development services to our customers. You will be working in our US office, located in Bellevue, WA, in a small team and have regular customer contact.



Your Responsibilities:

- Defining the best way to implement embedded system features with support from senior embedded engineers
- Creating custom Yocto distributions, layers, and recipes
- Customizing U-boot, the Linux kernel, and device drivers
- Developing or customizing board support packages (BSP) for our customers' custom hardware to provide additional functionality: system updates, security, boot optimization, etc.
- Scripting and developing middleware with Bash, Python, C, or C++
 

What to expect after the VIE program: Witekio sees the VIE program as a long-term investment, and several of our current software engineers are ex-VIEs. So if your mission is successful, the adventure could continue in our International Talent Program!


What Witekio has to offer:

- Exposure across a variety of projects and industries,
- International environment with teams distributed across 4 countries (France, Germany, the UK, and the US) and inter-office mobility opportunities,
- Culture of mentoring and learning,
 

Recruitment Process:

- Introductory call with a recruiter
- Technical assessment on the CodinGame platform
- Technical interview
- Director interview
Optionnal: a quick chat with one of our VIEs for additional questions you may have
